DESCRIPTION:
Good morning! Short and sweet today.
It's working...
Much like
[Talking Teen Barbie](http://www.nytimes.com/1992/10/21/business/company-news-mattel-says-it-erred-teen-talk-barbie-turns-silent-on-math.html)
of old, Trump declared, "
[Who knew health care could be so complicated](http://www.cnn.com/2017/02/27/politics/trump-health-care-complicated/)
!"
While that statement is rageful-despair-inducing, the admission is also a victory in the fight to not have people's lives destroyed through a health care repeal.
...so let's keep going
This morning let's revisit forcing the Republicans to confront the intolerable conflicts of interest and deceptions of their man in the White House. The House Judiciary Committee votes (and plans to bury) HR 111 today.
[Here](http://tinyletter.com/FiveMinutes/letters/your-five-minute-action-item-today-monday-feb-27)
is more about it.
Your task
Please tweet the Republican members of the judiciary committee (and the Democratic ones if you like, too) THIS MORNING. If you're not on Twitter you can call your rep if you haven't yet - details in
[yesterday's letter](http://tinyletter.com/FiveMinutes/letters/your-five-minute-action-item-today-monday-feb-27)
